dismissalText.commentary: Tawanda Mupariwa st Sangakkara b Muralidaran 0 (3b 0x4 0x6 4m) SR: 0

commentPreTextItems.html: six needed off the last ball. Can he pull this one off?

commentTextItems.html: gone!! so near, yet so far! charges down the track but misses a straight ball, Sangakkara fumbles it the first time but recovers well to take down the stumps. It's referred to the third umpire and the batsman is short of his ground.  Sri Lanka have won a thriller, by just five runs!

commentPostTextItems.html: What a match! Zimbabwe were down and out at the end of the second ODI but they have given their critics a sound reply here by pushing Sri Lanka to the finish. Zimbabwe were the favourites to win this game after Masakadza and Sibanda gave them a superb start, and the 68-run partnership between Taibu and Masakdza had more or less sealed it for the home team. But timely breakthroughs by Mendis and Kulasekara gave Sri Lanka a sniff at pulling it back. Mendis proved expensive, and went for 11 in the penultimate over. With ten required off the final over, it was anybody's game, but Matsikenyeri's dismissal off the very first ball proved decisive and settled the game for Sri Lanka.
Hamilton Masakadza is the Man of the Match for his riveting 77. It almost proved match-winning.
Well that's all we have from here folks! Thanks for tuning in and lets hope the remaining games live up to the thrill and excitement of this one.
On behalf of everyone at Cricinfo, goodbye!

headshotImage.longCaption: Farveez Maharoof player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Farveez Maharoof c Utseya b Mupariwa 14 (8b 2x4 0x6 11m) SR: 175

dismissalComment.html: gone! that was bowled full on middle and off, Maharoof drives that uppishly and straight to extra cover where Utseya completes an easy catch. Mupariwa finishes with four wickets!

headshotImage.caption: Thilan Thushara  player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Thilan Thushara  player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Hamilton Masakadza c Kulasekara b Thushara 77 (71b 7x4 2x6 95m) SR: 108.45

dismissalComment.html: gone!! goes for another big one, gets a thick outside edge that flies away towards third man where Kulasekara takes a well judged catch. Sri Lanka have struck, but is it too late? Masakadza departs for a potentially decisive 77

headshotImage.caption: Thilan Thushara  player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Thilan Thushara  player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Vusi Sibanda c Sangakkara b Thushara 25 (37b 0x4 1x6 54m) SR: 67.56

dismissalComment.html: gone!! that was short outside off, Sibanda fishes for it and tries to play at it with hard hands, hardly any footwork, gets a thick outside edge to Sangakkara who makes no mistake. Sri Lanka strike, finally! What a spirited innings by Sibanda!

dismissalText.commentary: Tatenda Taibu b Kulasekara 31 (38b 1x4 0x6 55m) SR: 81.57

dismissalComment.html: gone!! slower ball bowled full on middle, tries to swing it away towards mid wicket, misses, and the stumps take a beating

dismissalText.commentary: Elton Chigumbura b Mendis 3 (4b 0x4 0x6 6m) SR: 75

dismissalComment.html: bowled im!! comes down the track and tries to flay a quicker one, misses completely, and the off stump is out of the ground. What a timely wicket!

headshotImage.longCaption: Muttiah Muralitharan player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Stuart Matsikenyeri lbw b Muralidaran 19 (10b 1x4 1x6 18m) SR: 190

dismissalComment.html: gone!! he was struck in line with middle stump, no doubts there, the umpire raises his finger and there is dead silence around the ground

headshotImage.caption: Ajantha Mendis player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Ajantha Mendis player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Chamu Chibhabha b Mendis 0 (2b 0x4 0x6 5m) SR: 0

dismissalComment.html: bowled im!! Chibhabha went for a big sweep, missed it completely, and the ball crashed into middle and off stump

dismissalText.commentary: Sean Williams not out 2 (3b 0x4 0x6 9m) SR: 66.66

headshotImage.caption: Muttiah Muralitharan player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Muttiah Muralitharan player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Tawanda Mupariwa st Sangakkara b Muralidaran 0 (3b 0x4 0x6 4m) SR: 0

dismissalComment.html: gone!! so near, yet so far! charges down the track but misses a straight ball, Sangakkara fumbles it the first time but recovers well to take down the stumps. It's referred to the third umpire and the batsman is short of his ground.  Sri Lanka have won a thriller, by just five runs!

stories.title: Zimbabwe spark but Sri Lanka make it 3-0
stories.subTitle: Zimbabwe v Sri Lanka, 3rd ODI, Harare
stories.seoTitle: Zimbabwe spark but Sri Lanka make it 3-0
stories.summary: A match reduced to 28 overs produced the series' most compelling game in Harare, and the first performance by Zimbabwe to cause Sri Lanka a headache, but Sri Lanka nevertheless made it three wins out of three
